  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. As an accountant, the defendant held a position of financial responsibility and violated a fiduciary duty for personal gain. However, I must weigh the severity of this offense against significant mitigating factors: the defendant has no prior criminal record, and they have already demonstrated remorse and taken actionable responsibility by partially repaying the stolen funds. A lengthy prison sentence would severely hinder the defendant's ability to complete restitution and reintegrate as a productive member of society. Therefore, a brief period of incarceration is warranted to serve as a general deterrent and appropriate punishment for the breach of trust, which will be followed by a period of supervised probation to ensure full restitution is finalized.",
  "verdict": 6
